         <td colspan="2" style="border-top:2px solid #336699"> <a name="exit-pages"><h1>Exit Pages</h1></a> <img src="http://old.statcounter.com/images/features/exitpages.gif" alt="Exit Pages" class="image_border" border="3" width="396" height="199"> <br><br> Opposite to the entry pages, are exit pages - pages your visitors use to leave your site. No webmaster needs to be told the importance of knowing where their visitors are abandoning their site! This tool shows you the most common Exit Pages, allowing you to optimise those pages to keep visitors on your site. <br><br> </td> 
        </tr> 
